dataIdInfo.idPurp: This layer contains a detailed boundary of Texas with county boundaries. This polygon file was designed for medium scale thematic mapping and analysis.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: The spatial data originated from the US Census Bureau and are current as of 2010. The Texas county boundaries were exported from the Census US county 1:500,000 data and the census attributes were deleted. Attributes were further modified to include only county name, state abbreviation, population, area information, and FIPS code information. The coordinate system of this data is WGS 1984.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: Center for Geospatial Technology, Texas Tech University US Census Bureau
